==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*μέγας / megas / meg'-as

===Etymology===
*Including the prolonged forms, femine [[μεγάλη]] megalē, plural [[μέγάλοι]] megaloi, etc.; compare also [[μέγιστος]] {{GG|3176}}, [[μείζων]] {{GG|3187}} 

===Adjective===
'''μέγας'''

#[[big]] (literally or figuratively, in a very wide application): *(+ fear) exceedingly, [[great]] (-est), [[high]], large, loud, [[mighty]], + (be) sore (afraid), strong, X to years.

===References===
*[[Strong's concordance]] number:  [http://www.biblestudytools.net/Lexicons/Greek/grk.cgi?number=3173&version=kjv G3173] 

